âœ… Second Law of Thermodynamics

Heat cannot spontaneously flow from a colder body to a hotter body without external work.

âœ… Introduces entropy (disorder)
âœ… Heat flows hot â†’ cold naturally
âœ… No engine can be 100% efficient

Two famous statements:

âœ… Kelvinâ€“Planck Statement

No heat engine can convert all heat into work.

âœ… Clausius Statement

Heat cannot flow from cold to hot without work.

âœ… Entropy Concept

Entropy of an isolated system always increases or remains constant; it never decreases.

